Package: reproducr
Title: Computational Reproducibility Auditing for R Projects
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ndoh", "Penn", email = "ndohpenn9@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0003-9054-465X"))
Description: Audits R scripts for reproducibility risk beyond what 'renv'
    provides. Scans scripts for qualified package::function calls, checks them
    against a curated database of known breaking changes across popular CRAN
    packages, flags stochastic calls lacking set.seed(), and detects
    locale-sensitive operations. Supports baseline certification of analytical
    outputs so that silent numerical drift can be detected across package
    upgrades or platform changes. Generates human-readable audit reports
    suitable for academic submission or pharmaceutical QC workflows. Designed
    to complement 'renv', not replace it: 'renv' locks your packages;
    'reproducr' tells you whether locking them is actually enough.
